subject: resource/The_Trusts_Arena
object: The Trusts Arena is an indoor arena located in Waitakere City, Auckland, New Zealand.  It is a multi-purpose stadium that primarily holds sports events and music concerts. The Arena was opened by the Prime Minister Helen Clark on 11 September 2004.The Stadium Arena has hosted the New Zealand Breakers in the past, the Netball World Championships in November 2007 and the Auckland Darts Masters in August 2015. It holds 4,901 people and was built in 2004.
